<h2>Common Questions About Eco-Friendly Shopping</h2>

<h3>Are eco-friendly products really better?</h3>

<p>Yes! While some greenwashing exists, genuinely eco-friendly products reduce waste, use renewable materials, and often last longer than conventional alternatives. The key is doing your research and choosing certified products.</p>

<h3>Aren't sustainable products more expensive?</h3>

<p>Initially, yes—but the total cost of ownership is often lower. A PHP 300 stainless steel straw lasts 10+ years, while disposable straws cost PHP 50-100 per month. That's PHP 6,000-12,000 saved over a decade!</p>

<h3>How do I know if a product is truly eco-friendly?</h3>

<p>Look for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Specific material information (not vague "eco-friendly" claims)</li>
<li>Certifications from recognized organizations</li>
<li>Transparency about manufacturing process</li>
<li>Detailed disposal/end-of-life instructions</li>
<li>Honest reviews from verified buyers</li>
</ul>

<h3>Can one person really make a difference?</h3>

<p>Absolutely! If every Filipino replaced just one plastic item with a sustainable alternative, we'd divert millions of tons of plastic from landfills and oceans annually. Your choices inspire others and create demand for eco-friendly products.</p>

